## Blocks vs Code Layout

This README uses two different views of the project:

1. Enabled blocks: what was selected when this project was generated
2. Code layout: where the generated code lives inside the package

They are related, but they are not the same thing.

Examples:

- the HTTP runtime is a block, and its code lives under `{{ package_name }}/runtimes/http/`
- the PostgreSQL integration is a block, and its code lives mostly under `{{ package_name }}/infra/db/`
- the templating component is a block, and its code lives under `{{ package_name }}/infra/templating/` and `{{ package_name }}/protocols/templating/`
- the users feature is a block, and its code lives under `{{ package_name }}/features/users/`

